# vendor/binaries.manifest — pinned upstream DOS binaries fetched by
# scripts/fetch-vendor-binaries.sh. Mirror of vendor/sources.manifest's
# pin-by-hash discipline, but for redistributable pre-built binaries
# rather than git clones.
#
# Format (whitespace-separated, one entry per line, '#' for comments):
#
#     <path>  <url>  <sha256>
#
# <path>    destination path relative to repo root
# <url>     canonical fetch URL. If it ends in `#<member>`, the URL is a
#           zip archive and `<member>` is the path inside the archive to
#           extract to <path>.
# <sha256>  64-char hex digest of the bytes that should land at <path>
#           after the fetch + (optional) unzip step. The script verifies
#           against this before considering the file done.
#
# License notes — the .doc / COPYING / .lsm / .txt files that legally
# must accompany each binary stay tracked in git (see vendor/<name>/.gitignore
# negations). Only the binaries themselves are managed here.
#
# Provenance: each entry mirrors what's documented in vendor/<name>/README.md.
# If you change a URL or pin, update the README in lockstep.

